From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 18:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: pci-init step trace (debug only)

Diagnostic-only. On Flint 3 (IPQ5332 + QCN6274) loading ath12k wedges a
CPU's timer (RCU stall) BEFORE ath12k_pci_probe prints its first line, so
the probe-step trace (099) captures nothing. Bracket pci_register_driver in
ath12k_pci_init with pr_emerg prints to tell whether the module-init path
reaches and returns from driver registration (which synchronously probes).

Remove before merge.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c
@@ -1911,7 +1911,9 @@ int ath12k_pci_init(void)
 {
 	int ret;

+	pr_emerg("ath12k INIT-STEP[A] calling pci_register_driver\n");
 	ret = pci_register_driver(&ath12k_pci_driver);
+	pr_emerg("ath12k INIT-STEP[B] pci_register_driver returned %d\n", ret);
 	if (ret) {
 		pr_err("failed to register ath12k pci driver: %d\n",
 		       ret);
